snippet: Bombings and other attacks have killed more than 250 people since the start of Ramadan on July 10.
abstract: Seven car bombs explode on busy commercial streets in different Shiite areas of Baghdad, killing at least 35 people; no immediate claim of responsibility is made for coordinated attacks that are part of wave of violence that has left more than 250 people dead since start of Ramadan in July.
lead_paragraph: Bombings and other attacks have killed more than 250 people since the start of Ramadan on July 10.
